72}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:598"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Bcl-xL", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9935139417648315, "span": {"begin": 677, "end": 683}}, {"id": ["mesh:D064420"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "apoptosis-inducing", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9702005386352539, "span": {"begin": 706, "end": 724}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:581"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Bax", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.6284151077270508, "span": {"begin": 733, "end": 736}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "spermatogonia", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.9034046530723572, "span": {"begin": 781, "end": 794}}], "text": "Spermatocytes are differentiated from spermatogonial stem cells via random proliferation, differentiation, and synchronized mitoses with several stages [Rooij, 2001]. In each&nbsp;step&nbsp;of the spermatogonial differentiation, different molecular mechanisms are&nbsp;activated in the testis [Rooij, 2001;&nbsp;de Kretser et al., 2016]. The stem cell factor (SCF) genes are involved in differentiation into A1 spermatogonia. The expression of cyclin D2 is regulated in the epithelial stage VIII when the aligned spermatogonia differentiate into A1 spermatogonia [Rooij, 2001]. Upon the apoptosis of spermatogonia, overexpression of the apoptosis-inhibiting proteins Bcl-2 and Bcl-xL and deficiency of the apoptosis-inducing protein Bax have been shown to cause an accumulation of spermatogonia in the testis, leading to apoptosis of all cells [Rooij, 2001].", "timestamp": "Fri May 15 21:42:02 +0000 2026"}